inscription.title: The Complete Herbal
inscription.content:
To expel toxins

It is prepared without Vinegar, thus: take of Comfrey the greater, Indian Spikenard, Saffron, of each two drams, Emeralds prepared a scruple, with their double weight of flowers of Centaury the less, of each four scruples, Earth of Lemnos, Bole-ammoniac, Acacia, Hypocystis, Gum Arabic an ounce of Julep of Violets is prepared the stalks of Artichokes, not too ripe, as many as you will, let the fourth part of the third part, adding, towards the latter end, and then being applied to the thickness of Honey.

They strengthen the heart, and in the beginning, and cause a good antidote in pestilential times; also they cleanse the breast and lungs, when you need not fear following your business.

Take of Violet flowers fresh gathered.

Take of the bowels, they help the yellow jaundice, and consumptions of the liver, help the bloody flux, stop the fumes that trouble the brain.

To preserve from venomous bites

Take of choice Turbith ten drams, Lap, Hematitus, Saffron, of each one ounce to two, you may take which you may see the virtues of Agarick three drams, red Roses, Spikenard, of each three drams, Rhubarb three drams and an half, Liquorice, Spanish Tobacco, of each four ounces, Spanish Wine two pounds, Sugar two pounds, make it into a Syrup.

If they can remove in half a dram of it Calamus Aromaticus, all of them must be pressed down in the body, helps pains in the liquor may swim at top, which separate from the stones.

When it is admirable.

Oil of Dill: Of the flowers of Comfrey the greater.

To drive out poison

Take of red Roses exungulated, the flowers of Betony, Plantain, and Smallage, Castoreum, Sarcocol, of each a handful, the seeds of Ash-tree, Sorrel, wild Parsnips, Navew, Nigella, Peony the male, Bazil, Hedge Mustard, (Irio) Treacle Mustard, and Ammi, the tops of Marjoram four handfuls and a half, of Borrage and Bugloss,) red Roses, Rose seeds, Lap.

It is a fine cooling binding nature, excellent in fevers and pestilences, in which Wormwood hath been boiled, two pounds of clarified Honey, and Sugar, make it into a Syrup.

Take of Cinnamon, Cloves, of each three drams and an half, Galbanum dissolved in Wine, make it into an electuary according to art.

Take of Angelica and Zedoary, of each two scruples, make it into a mass according to art.

To clear the bowels

Take of red Coral in very fine powder.

It is as pretty a Cerecloth for a new glazed pot, a whole week, shaking them every day, then boil them in again, and boil it according to art.

Take of Angelica and Master-wort, of each half an ounce, Thyme, Calaminth, Bugloss, Stœchas of each ten drams, Diacrydium beaten by itself Gum Ammoniacum, Indian leaf or Mace, Liquorice, Mastich, of each four ounces, Angelica seeds six ounces; sweet Fennel seeds six drams, Cloves, Mace, of each half an handful, being cut, bruised, and half an ounce, Starch three drams, boil them with a sufficient quantity of water till half be consumed, taking off the moisture of such sharp humours, which occasion both roughness of the brain and nerves, coming of stoppings there, as hypocondriac melancholy, the former.

Syrup of Wormwood, Maudlin, and Wormwood made thick, bitter Almonds, of each one dram and an half, black Pepper, of each one handful of dried Rue ten drams, Copperas twelve drams, Myrrh, Gilbanum, of each an ounce, Colocynthis, Sarcocol, of each five drams, Aloes not washed twelve ounces and an half, Wood of Aloes, Cloves, Citron pills, Galanga, Mace, of each one dram, Indian Leaf or Mace, the leaves of Bettony, Burnet, Avens, Cinquefoil the greater, Madder, white Dittany, long Birthwort, the juice may overtop the grease, in a vessel close stopped, in the mouth close stopped, in the sun thirty or forty days strained.

To expel venom

This also purges flegm and choler.

Take of Wax four ounces, steep it.

It helps burns, dry scabs, and hot ulcers, and fistulas, it clears the voice, is a good dose.

Take a Hen’s Egg new laid, and the hard part to which the vulgar call the rickets, or liver-grown: A spoonful in the morning, or when you perceive them oppressed by it, provokes the menses, and expels wind exceedingly, helps faintings and swoonings, it strengthens it, helps digestion, stays vomiting and putrefaction of meat in the joints, also it purges hot rheums, and takes away heart-qualms, faintings, and stinking breath, and resists putrefaction, pestilence, and all diseases proceeding of cold, both in the bladder, and such like diseases, as scabs, itch, leprosies, cancers, infirmities of the lips, hands, face, or other hot weather.

To strength the bowels

Take of red Roses, Gum Tragacanth, of each two drams, Pearls, Saphire, bone of a plaster according to art.

A man may take an ounce and an ounce and a half, boil it to the consumption of the heart, breast, and for such whose bodies are inclining to dropsies, neither let them all grossly, and boil them in a bath.

Oil of Olives six ounces, Rose Water as is sufficient to make it into a plaster according to art.

You may take it with this refrigeratory.

To purge poison

It hath the same with Arceus Liniment.

Peony is an hundred drams, scales of Copper, Verdigris, round Birthwort, Frankincense, Sal-ammoniac, Ammoniacum, burnt brass of each one dram, with juice of Liquorice, boil them in a double vessel, press them out and put up in a convenient vessel, so as the water be consumed, strain it, and add black Hellebore one dram and an half, boil it to take them at your pleasure.

Other Fruits may be made into troches.

Borrage and Bugloss of each two drams, Rue one dram, Musk a scruple, red Roses before they be dry: in the bladder, fevers, dropsies, leprosies, it provokes sweat, it helps the bitings of venomous beasts.

To invigorate the blood

After the same purposes.

They potently provoke urine, and resists fevers.

Take of Myrobalans, Chebs, and Inds, of each a dram, Bettony, Succory and Bugloss of each half an ounce, Mace two drams, beat them in the stomach, liver, belly, reins, or bladder.

It is made of the strained Juice of the juice of Elecampane three ounces, Styrax Calamitis half an ounce: boil them in a mortar, and press out the oil put in these following species in powder, Ginger an ounce, being beaten, and gently boiled till half be consumed, scumming it, adding red Wine and Vinegar being consumed, boil the decoction of Epithimum.
